/* =====================================================================
   TRANSACTION TRACKER — DATASET FILE  (dataset.js)
   =====================================================================
   This is the ONLY file you should ever need to open and edit by hand.
   index.html itself never needs to be touched again — it just loads
   this file automatically every time it's opened (via a <script
   src="dataset.js"> tag), so there's no risk of accidentally breaking
   any of the app's actual code while you're updating your data.

   Keep this file in the SAME folder as index.html at all times.

   WHAT'S IN HERE
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------
   1. DATASETS              — every tracker and all of its records.
   2. DEFAULT_DATASET_ID     — which dataset opens automatically.
   3. DEFAULT_APP_STATE      — whether Secure Input starts locked, and
                               with what password, the very first time
                               this is opened in a browser.

   HOW THE TWO DOWNLOAD BUTTONS RELATE TO THIS FILE
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------
   • "Download Current Dataset Update" (Settings → Active Dataset)
     downloads a small .txt containing just ONE updated dataset object
     (whichever one you currently have selected), reflecting any
     add/edit/delete changes you made through the app. Open that .txt,
     copy the object, and manually paste it over the matching dataset
     object inside the DATASETS array below — a precise, surgical
     update.

   • "Download Full App Data" downloads a complete, ready-to-use
     REPLACEMENT for this exact file — every dataset's latest data,
     plus the current Secure Input lock/password state, all already
     assembled. When you click it, just delete this old dataset.js
     and put the newly downloaded one in its place (rename it to
     dataset.js). No manual copy-pasting required for that one.
   ===================================================================== */

/* =====================================================================
   DATASET CONFIGURATION
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------
   This app no longer imports/exports Excel files. Instead, every
   tracker ("dataset") you want to see lives right here in the code.
   Open this file in a text editor whenever you want to add, edit, or
   remove a dataset — then just reopen index.html in the browser.

   Each dataset is an object with:
     id              - unique short id, no spaces, used internally
     label           - shown in the Settings dropdown
     evidenceFolder  - the folder name (placed next to this index.html
                       file) that holds this dataset's evidence images.
                       Leave it as '' if every record below already
                       embeds its own image via "proofData".
     items           - the array of transaction records. Each record
                       needs: d (datetime, "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM"), t
                       ("taken" or "returned"), a (amount), desc.
                       For the evidence image, give EITHER:
                         proofName: 'exact-file-name.png'   (looked up
                            inside ./<evidenceFolder>/ at view time)
                       OR
                         proofData: 'data:image/png;base64,....'  (a
                            self-contained image, no extra files
                            needed at all — handy for small/sample
                            datasets).

   HOW TO ADD A NEW DATASET
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------
   1. Duplicate one of the objects in the DATASETS array below.
   2. Give it a new unique "id" and a friendly "label".
   3. If you're using image files, put them in a new folder next to
      this index.html (e.g. "My_Evidences") and set evidenceFolder to
      that folder's exact name.
   4. Fill in the "items" array with your records.
   5. (Optional) Set DEFAULT_DATASET_ID below to that new dataset's id
      if you want it to open automatically every time the file loads.
   6. Save this file and reopen it in the browser — the new dataset
      will appear in Settings → Active Dataset.

   Any edits you make later from inside the app (adding / editing /
   deleting records through the UI) are saved in this browser's local
   storage on top of the data below, per dataset. Use the
   "Reset to Default Data" button in Settings to wipe those local
   edits and go back to exactly what is written in this file.
   ===================================================================== */

